OL,3,CMinister quells conscription rumours
OL,4,Cfollowing suggestion of 'citizen army'
OL,6,FThe UK's has dispelled talk of
OL,7,Fintroducing conscription to the Army
OL,8,Fif Nato goes to war with Russia.
OL,9,FFrontbencher James Heappey said the UK
OL,10,F"long had plans" for "mobilising
OL,11,Fvolunteers" in the event that Britain
OL,12,Fdoes enter a new conflict, but
OL,13,Fstressed that "nobody is thinking"
OL,14,Fabout bringing back conscription.JIt
OL,15,Fcomes after comments made by General
OL,16,FSir Patrick Sanders, the outgoing
OL,17,F(CGS), who said the country should
OL,18,F"train and equip" a "citizen army".
