OL,3,CMinister quells conscription rumours
OL,4,Cfollowing suggestion of 'citizen army'
OL,6,FHe pointed to Sweden introducing a
OL,7,Fform of military service for its
OL,8,Fpopulation, and added said at least
OL,9,F45,000 British reservists and citizens
OL,10,Fshould be trained up in the next three
OL,11,Fyears to top-up the current army size
OL,12,Fof 74,000.JNo 10 ruled out any
OL,13,Fsuggestion that conscription was under
OL,14,Fconsideration, saying there were "no
OL,15,Fplans" to change the British
OL,16,Fmilitary's "proud tradition of being a
OL,17,Fvoluntary force".JMr Heappey backed up
OL,18,Fthat sentiment on Thursday, tweeting:
OL,19,F"There are three issues being
OL,20,Fconflated into one in response to the
OL,21,FCGS's speech on Wednesday.J"Firstly,
OL,22,Fconscription. Nobody has ever
OL,23,Fmentioned it, nobody is even thinking
OL,24,Fabout it. CGS didn't say it. It is all
OL,25,Fnonsense."
